"Webb S.M., Jaksch D., McPheat R.A., Drage E., Vasekova E., Limão-Vieira P., Mason N.J., Smith K.M.","High-resolution, temperature dependant, fourier transform infrared spectroscopy of CF3I",2005,"Journal of Quantitative Spectroscopy and Radiative Transfer","94","3-4",,"425","438",,,10.1016/j.jqsrt.2004.09.026,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-14944375388&partnerID=40&md5=bd9d4748693018fec4b17ba584f05f66","Department of Physics and Astronomy, The Open University, Walton hall, Milton Keynes, Bucks. MK7 6AA, United Kingdom; Space Science/Technology Department, Rutherford Appleton Laboratory, Chilton, Didcot, Oxon OX11 0QX, United Kingdom; Departamento de Física, CEFITEC, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, Quinta da Torre, P-2829-516 Caparica, Portugal","Webb, S.M., Department of Physics and Astronomy, The Open University, Walton hall, Milton Keynes, Bucks. MK7 6AA, United Kingdom; Jaksch, D., Department of Physics and Astronomy, The Open University, Walton hall, Milton Keynes, Bucks. MK7 6AA, United Kingdom; McPheat, R.A., Space Science/Technology Department, Rutherford Appleton Laboratory, Chilton, Didcot, Oxon OX11 0QX, United Kingdom; Drage, E., Department of Physics and Astronomy, The Open University, Walton hall, Milton Keynes, Bucks. MK7 6AA, United Kingdom; Vasekova, E., Department of Physics and Astronomy, The Open University, Walton hall, Milton Keynes, Bucks. MK7 6AA, United Kingdom; Limão-Vieira, P., Departamento de Física, CEFITEC, Universidade Nova de Lisboa, Quinta da Torre, P-2829-516 Caparica, Portugal; Mason, N.J., Department of Physics and Astronomy, The Open University, Walton hall, Milton Keynes, Bucks. MK7 6AA, United Kingdom; Smith, K.M., Space Science/Technology Department, Rutherford Appleton Laboratory, Chilton, Didcot, Oxon OX11 0QX, United Kingdom","CF3I is being considered as a replacement for some of the global warming gases currently used in the plasma industry, however before this compound can be put into wide-scale use the possible implications upon the atmosphere must be carefully considered. Calculations of global warming potentials of compounds require detailed information about the infrared absorption properties of a compound. High resolution Fourier transform infrared spectroscopy has been applied to CF3I to measure absolute infrared photo absorption cross-sections. These have been measured in the ranges (400-1400) cm-1 and (1900-2500) cm-1 at a resolution of 0.003 cm-1 for temperatures of 208.0, 251.6, 272.9 and 299.4 K over a range of pressures. Eight absorption features were observed across the measured range some of which lie within the atmospheric IR (800-1300 cm-1) window and hence may play a role in global warming. © 2004 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.","CF3I; Ftir; Global warming; Infrared spectroscopy","Atmospheric radiation; Global warming; Halogen compounds; Light absorption; Plasmas; Thermal effects; Global warming gases; Photo absorption; Plasma industry; Fourier transform infrared spectroscopy; atmospheric gas; infrared spectroscopy",,,,,,"Hansen, J., Sato, M., Ruedy, R., (1997) J. Geophys. Res., 102, p. 6831; Pinnock, S., Hurley, M.D., Shine, K.P., Wallington, T.J., Smyth, T.J., (1995) J. Geophys. Res., 100, p. 23227; Misra, A., Sees, J., Hall, L., Levy, R.A., Zaitsev, V.B., Aryusook, K., Ravindranath, C., Rufin, D., (1998) Mat. Lett., 34, p. 415; Ohtake, H., Ishihara, H., Fuse, T., Koshiishi, A., Samukawa, S., (2003) J. Vac. Sci. Technol. B, 21, p. 2142; Fieberg, J.E., Szabo, A., White, J.M., (1996) J. Chem. Soc. Faraday Trans., 92, p. 4739; Sanabia, J.E., Moore, J.H., Tossell, J.A., (2002) J. Chem. Phys., 116, p. 10402; Mason, N.J., Limao Vieira, P., Eden, S., Kendall, P., Pathak, S., Dawes, A., Tennyson, J., Spyrou, S.M., (2003) Int. J. Mass Spectrom., 223-224, p. 647; Atkinson, R., Baulch, D.L., Cox, R.A., Hampson, R.F., Kerr, J.A., Troe, J., (1992) J. Phys. Chem. Ref. Data, 21, p. 1125; Solomon, S., Burkholder, J.B., Ravishankara, A.R., Garcia, R.R., (1994)